      "instruction": "<p>Before you start cooking, take your <strong>steak</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it adjust to room temperature</p><p>Add your <strong>ground</strong> <strong>smoked paprika</strong>, <strong>cayenne pepper</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!), <strong>dried oregano</strong>,<strong> half </strong>your <strong>ground</strong> <strong>cumin </strong>(you'll use the rest later!), a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and a generous grind of <strong>black pepper</strong> to a plate and give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>Mexican-style</strong> <strong>spice blend</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1620220600738-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1620220600738-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1620220600738-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1620220600738-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1620220600738-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Pat your <strong>pork loin steak[s]</strong> dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Rub with a little <strong>vegetable oil</strong>,<strong> </strong>then add<strong> </strong>to the <strong>Mexican-style</strong> <strong>spice blend</strong> and turn several times until they're fully coated and set aside</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1620220612869-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1620220612869-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1620220612869-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1620220612869-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1620220612869-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Drain and rinse your <strong>kidney beans</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>drained kidney beans</strong> and <strong>remaining ground cumin</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until the skins have softened</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1620220621924-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1620220621924-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1620220621924-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1620220621924-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1620220621924-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely slice your <strong>shallot[s]</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>tomato[es]<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span></strong>roughly</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1620220650770-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1620220650770-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1620220650770-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1620220650770-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1620220650770-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Transfer the<strong> softened kidney beans</strong> to a bowl and set aside to cool</p><p>Return the pan to the heat on high with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>and once hot add the <strong>spiced</strong> <strong>steak </strong>and cook for 5-6 min on each side or until browned and cooked through</p><p>Once done, transfer the cooked steak to a clean chopping board, cover with a clean tea towel and leave to rest for 2 min – this is your<strong> Mexican-style spiced pork steak</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1620220665197-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1620220665197-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1620220665197-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1620220665197-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1620220665197-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Cut your<strong> cucumber</strong> into quarters lengthways, then slice finely</p><p>Strip your <strong>mint leaves</strong> from their stems and chop them roughly, discard the stems</p><p>Chop your <strong>coriander</strong> finely, including the stalks</p><p>Roll your <strong>lime[s]</strong> with your hand on a hard surface (to release more juice) and cut in half</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1620220684764-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1620220684764-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1620220684764-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1620220684764-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1620220684764-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped tomato</strong>,<strong> cucumber</strong>, <strong>shallot</strong>,<strong> coriander </strong>and the juice<strong> </strong>of <strong>half</strong> the<strong> lime[s]</strong>, a generous drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>to the<strong> </strong>softened kidney beans with a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper </strong>– this is your <strong>kidney bean salad</strong></p><p>Combine the <strong>chopped mint</strong>,<strong> yoghurt </strong>and the<strong> </strong>juice from the<strong> remaining lime </strong>in a small bowl</p><p>Season with a crack of <strong>black</strong> <strong>pepper</strong> – this is your<strong> limey mint yoghurt</strong></p><p>Trim then, slice your <strong>spring onion[s]</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1620220713864-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1620220713864-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1620220713864-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1620220713864-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1620220713864-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Slice the <strong>rested steak[s] </strong>finely on a clean board</p><p>Serve the <strong>sliced</strong> <strong>steak</strong> over the <strong>limey mint yoghurt</strong> with the <strong>kidney bean salad</strong> to the side</p><p>Sprinkle over the <strong>sliced spring onion</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
      "media": {
        "images": []
      }
    }
